<hl>
<seg id=1> Cote D'Ivoire Financial Minister Declares Evident Growth Recovery in West African Economy </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Abidjan, January 18th (Linghu Daocheng). On the 17th, Engoland, the Cote D'Ivoire Economic and Financial Minister, declared that the economies of the West Africa Economy and Currency Association members had resumed an increase and overall were in good condition. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> At the businessmen's meeting held by France-Cote D'Ivoire businessman club, Engoland said that the annual average economic rate of increase in members of West Africa Economy and Currency Association had leaped to 5.9% in 1996, and 6.3% in 1997, while it was only 2.6% in 1994. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said that West African countries had reformed their imbalance between import and export and public investment, surplus had increased great deal, and the budget deficit had declined sharply and accounted for only 1.3% of the Gross Domestic Product. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> When talking about the effect of the unit of currency in Europe to the African Franc, Engoland expressed that people do not need to worry about the future of Africa Franc. </seg>
<seg id=6> He said that the economy of West Africa Economy and Currency Association members was improving and in the near future the African Franc would not be devalued to such a great extent as the 50% it had in January of 1994. </seg>
</p>
